{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f823ae52-7032-44ca-8cdc-2ac984a9d008","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed *before* them. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFixing by swapping the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01JB7buom8Ppz4dvv2PqNUAL","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-035c9c1dce1f49cdb9a89e7f0c514645/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-035c9c1dce1f49cdb9a89e7f0c514645/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"792a8bbc-347a-439a-bb1c-bb60022fce58","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed before them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` — opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, but `Domain.fs` hasn't been compiled yet\n2. `Domain.fs` — defines the types\n3. `Program.fs` — uses both\n\nThe fix is to reorder so `Domain.fs` comes first, then `Services.fs`, then `Program.fs`.","outputTokens":384,"requestId":"27CE:16A66F:5EDE882:664CC12:69FBE281"},"id":"ce2dfa6e-5b0f-4a61-b14f-95b51799a5d8","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:53:29.056Z","parentId":"d8ab4598-3670-444a-a20d-a34dda62e8cc"}
